  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold text-ink tracking-wide uppercase mb-10">
        Frequently Asked <span class="text-accent">Questions</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8" open>
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is an automatic tray loader?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>An automatic tray loader places product into trays without manual labor. The system combines a tray denester, product infeed conveyor, placement mechanism (pick-and-place, servo gantry, or delta robot), and outfeed conveyor. Speeds range from 20 to 300+ placements per minute depending on the technology and product type.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is the difference between pick-and-place and robotic tray loading?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Pick-and-place systems use fixed-motion mechanisms , cam-driven or servo gantry , that follow repeatable paths at high speed. Robotic systems use delta or articulated robots with programmable motion paths and vision guidance. Pick-and-place suits high-speed, low-SKU operations. Robotic suits high-SKU, frequent-changeover environments where random product infeed is common.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How fast can an automatic tray loader run?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Cam-driven systems reach 200–300+ placements per minute for small, uniform products. Servo gantry systems run 60–150 placements per minute. Single delta robots handle 80–200 picks per minute. Multi-robot cells with 2–6 robots in series achieve 200–800+ combined placements per minute. Actual speed depends on product size, weight, fragility, and tray configuration.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What industries use automatic tray loading?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Bakery and snack foods (cookies, crackers, bars), fresh produce (berries, tomatoes), ready meals and prepared foods, meat and poultry, confectionery, and pharmaceutical blister packing all use automatic tray loading. Any operation placing discrete products into thermoformed or pre-formed trays benefits from automation when volumes exceed 30 trays per minute or when manual labor availability is constrained.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
